      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b09",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1059464737,
      "version": 4032,
      "versionNonce": 1109954337,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776575149613,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "At the end there will be a final prompt which will be passed to the model. Now you have\nthe question about the structure of the model.\n\nIn the settings, user should be able to add the different models of the fal ai, user will\nbe adding the curl command of the model and that will be added there for the use in\nthe various parts, but as a whole that is added there. Not only the simple model will\nbe added, but also the sub features of it, will also be added and given the options to\nthe user based on the curl command and the options that model is giving, like quality,\nnumber of images... they calls that additional settings, so once added, it will be shown\nlike we do in n8n.\n\nAnother thing is that, as the end mockup prompt here will be made, will be based on the\nstyling and the arrangements type things for the product, and the final image/images\nare being made with the combination of the users raw product/products and the the\nprompt, so you have to give an option to the user to make the template of it, after\nthe result. In that template at that time, add the image made(or if M2, then make\nthem select the best image), and the prompt at that time in the template, so user\nknow about the result he will get.",
      "fontSize": 4.9281536055326045,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "At the end there will be a final prompt which will be passed to the model. Now you have the question about the structure of the model.\n\nIn the settings, user should be able to add the different models of the fal ai, user will be adding the curl command of the model and that will be added there for the use in the various parts, but as a whole that is added there. Not only the simple model will be added, but also the sub features of it, will also be added and given the options to the user based on the curl command and the options that model is giving, like quality, number of images... they calls that additional settings, so once added, it will be shown like we do in n8n.\n\nAnother thing is that, as the end mockup prompt here will be made, will be based on the styling and the arrangements type things for the product, and the final image/images are being made with the combination of the users raw product/products and the the prompt, so you have to give an option to the user to make the template of it, after the result. In that template at that time, add the image made(or if M2, then make them select the best image), and the prompt at that time in the template, so user know about the result he will get.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
